{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6581-fails-java-run-org.seleniumhq.selenium-selenium-ie-driver-4.4.0-5685b8be\n\nThe Java-run regression itself appears to have been identified and patched on the preserved branch: the early failing runs show `Selenium_ie_driverTest > settingIeOptionsCapabilityAcceptsMapAndCapabilitiesValues()` failing because the test expected old IE options behavior (`human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T07-21-46-343433Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T07-22-11-945937Z.log`). Later reruns passed (`human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T07-24-24-846538Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T07-25-07-724070Z.log`), and native trace image verification also passed (`human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-06T07-23-26-710455Z.log`).\n\nThe most likely stage that caused the workflow to finish in failure was metadata/coverage verification, not the Java test fix. `generateMetadata` failed because the JVM test process could not load the Graal native-image agent: `Could not find agent library native-image-agent ... libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file` in `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-06T07-23-25-533975Z.log`. This matches the failed metrics in `stats/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-ie-driver/4.4.0/execution-metrics.json` and the missing dynamic-access data in `tests/src/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-ie-driver/4.4.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` (`0` total calls, no dynamic access).\n\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the test update against the assertion failures in the two failing `gradle-test` logs above.\n2. Re-run `generateMetadata` / verification in an environment where `native-image-agent` is installed and on the library path, then confirm dynamic-access coverage is produced.\n3. If metadata generation succeeds after the environment fix, keep the candidate test change; if it still fails, inspect the generated test report under `tests/src/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-ie-driver/4.4.0/build/reports/tests/test/` for any remaining behavioral mismatch."}}
